# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# packages/web — Environment Variables
#
# Mode files (.env.development, .env.staging, .env.production) are committed
# and provide all defaults automatically. You do NOT need to copy this file
# for normal local development.
#
# Create .env.local (git-ignored) ONLY to:
#   - Enable Sentry locally (add VITE_SENTRY_DSN)
#   - Override any mode file value for local testing
#
# Per-environment defaults are provided by Vite mode files:
#   .env.development  → loaded by `vite dev`
#   .env.staging      → loaded by `vite build --mode staging`
#   .env.production   → loaded by `vite build` / `vite build --mode production`
#
# ── CI/CD required secrets (GitHub Actions) ──────────────────────────────────
# FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_STAGING    → Firebase service account JSON (staging project)
# FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_PRODUCTION → Firebase service account JSON (production project)
# VITE_SENTRY_RELEASE                 → git SHA or semver tag injected at build time
#
# NOTE: VITE_SENTRY_DSN is NOT a secret — it is committed in .env.staging and
# .env.production (it is a public value that ships in the JS bundle).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Environment identity (AUTO-SET — do not set in .env.local unless testing) ─
# VITE_APP_ENV is injected automatically by Vite's mode files:
#   .env.development  → development
#   .env.staging      → staging
#   .env.production   → production
# You only need to set this manually to simulate a different environment locally.
# Values: development | staging | production
# VITE_APP_ENV=development

# ── Sentry ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# VITE_SENTRY_DSN: committed in .env.staging and .env.production.
# Set here ONLY to enable Sentry in local development.
# When absent, Sentry is disabled and no events are sent.
# VITE_SENTRY_DSN=https://<key>@o<org>.ingest.sentry.io/<project>

# Optional: ties events to a specific deploy/version in Sentry.
# Injected automatically by CI (github.sha). Leave empty locally.
# VITE_SENTRY_RELEASE=

# Fraction of performance transactions sent to Sentry (0.0 – 1.0).
# Set automatically by mode files: development=1, staging=0.5, production=0.1
# Override here to test a specific sample rate locally.
# VITE_SENTRY_TRACE_SAMPLE_RATE=1
